a Intensity dependent JSC of a monolayer Y6 device. The power exponent fitted to the data between 0.2 and 2 suns is 0.84, indicating a high number of bimolecular recombination events. b External quantum efficiencies (EQEs) of devices with active layers consisting of small ratios of donor, PTB7-Th, to acceptor, Y6. For such low donor content, EQEs are unexpectedly high. c Normalised transient absorption kinetics of exciton and charge species in blends of PTB7-Th:Y6 with ratios of 1:50 and 1:100. Pumped with 800 nm, 150 fs pulses at excitation density 1 × 1017 excitations/cm3. The exciton kinetics of both films, dashed lines, are matching, as are the rise times of the charge kinetics (orange and red lines), but the 1:50 blend shows slower charge recombination after 20 ps. The green-blue line shows the hole kinetics in the 1:50 blend, showing a gradual increase in hole population as excitons and charges in Y6 diffuse to the PTB7-Th.

Measurements were performed using a homebuilt experimental setup illuminated by an amplified Ti:sapphire laser, with pulse durations of 100–150 fs, centred around 800 nm and at a repetition rate of 3 kHz. The excitation pulses are generated either using this fundamental, or by using an optical parametric amplifier (TOPAS) with the 800 nm fundamental input and then chopped at f/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
